Academy_Award_for_Best_Picture_(1930s)	The awards were intended to honor different and equally important aspects of superior filmmaking , and in fact the judges and the studio bosses who sought to influence their decisions paid more attention to the latter - MGM head Louis B. Mayer , who had disliked the realism of King Vidor 's The Crowd , another of the nominees ( the third was Merian C. Cooper and Ernest B. Schoedsack 's Chang ) pressured the judges not to honor his own studio 's film , and to select Sunrise instead .	The name of the award becomes Best Picture in 1930 .	0







